despite concerns about its implications for freedom of expression the bangladeshi parliament approved the digital security act in september 2018
the law replaced the notorious information and  technology act which had also been used as a tool for silencing critical speech online
the act criminalizes various types of online speech ranging from defamatory messages to speech that injures religious values or sentiments introducing hefty fines
it also authorizes lengthy prison sentences for using the internet to create public unrest and for gathering sending or preserving classified government documents using a digital device
the editors council of bangladesh said that the act is against the freedom guaranteed by the constitution media freedom and freedom of speech
